    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and cut the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and roughly chop the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock powder</strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>beef stock</strong></p><p>Add a large handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Coat the <strong>beef strips</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated beef strips </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until browned</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>carrots</strong>,<strong> bay leaves</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and the <strong>beef stock</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>Irish beef stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the stew is cooking, chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the chopped potatoes to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside, reserve the pan for later</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and chop into small pieces</p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and add a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>spring onion </strong>and <strong>spring greens </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the spring greens are tender, add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> and a large splash of <strong>milk</strong> to the pot</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>colcannon</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/irish-beef-stew-with-colcannon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Irish beef stew</strong> with the<strong> colcannon </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: Feeling indulgent? Use the back of a spoon to make a well in the colcannon and add a knob of butter</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
